<div class="title-block" style="float:left; width:100%;">
<h3>3.	COMPREHENSIVE LAND USE PLAN PROJECT</h3>
</div>
<div class="expanded-content">
<p>
The purpose of the Comprehensive Land Use Plan (CLUP) is to ensure the First Nation lands are used in a sustainable way. We need to plan for the future by protecting and preserving the natural areas at the same time improving and maximizing the production of agricultural lands, designating areas for community development by zoning. The plan will also ensure the best practical choices for the use of land are made.
</p>
<div class="fancy-title title-border"style="float:left; width:100%;"><h3>3.1	Comprehensive Land Use Plan Phase I – 2015</h3></div>

<p>The first phase of the Comprehensive Land Use Plan (CLUP) Project was to develop a planning process for the First Nation planning groups to be used as a guide. The LPFN Lands Department coordinated gatherings and meetings with the program managers to build capacity in land use planning. 
The CLUP Working Group comprised of the Land Manager, Land Use Coordinator, Land Use Facilitator and Lands Portfolio Councilor. Responsibility of the Working Group was to organize and coordinate gatherings with the planning groups in developing a land use plan framework and process for Phase II. </p> 

 <div id="openDiv4"  style="display:none;" >
<p>
The CLUP Advisory Group comprised of the Long Plain First Nation Program Managers from Housing, Social Services, Economic Development, Health, Education, Public Works, Water and Sanitation, Land Management Departments and Stakeholders: Long Plain First Nation Trust and Arrowhead Development Corporation.</p>

<div class="fancy-title title-border style="float:left; width:100%;""><h3>3.2 Comprehensive Land Use Plan Phase II 2015-2016</h3></div>

<p>
The Comprehensive Land Use Plan (CLUP) Phase II focused on the developing a draft land use plan and setting goals and guiding principles for the developmental process. The goals of the CLUP Phase II Project were to develop a draft land use plan by:</p>

<ul class="content-listing">

<li> - Appointing and establishing the Working and Advisory groups by the Band Council (CLUP Working Group and Advisory Group). </li>
<li> - Developing terms of reference for the Working Group and Advisory Group;</li>
<li> - Developing a Vision Statement and Mission Statement for the First Nation as it relates to land use planning;    </li> 
<li> - Coordinating Program Managers and Stakeholders gatherings and workshops to discuss program areas in existing state and discuss future requirements of housing, economic, social, health, education, recreation, public works and infrastructure, land use, traditional and cultural development;</li>
<li> - Researching and collecting LPFN traditional and historical information;</li>
<li> - Developing a draft community profile; and </li>
<li> - Building capacity development in GIS mapping technology and data base. </li>
</ul>

<div class="fancy-title title-border" style="float:left; width:100%;"><h3>3.3 Comprehensive Land Use Plan Phase III2016 – 2017</h3></div>

<p>
The LPFN Lands Department submitted a new proposal to Lands and Economic Development Services Program, Indigenous and Northern Affairs Canada for the Comprehensive Land Use Plan Phase III Project.  The CLUP project will develop and provide the community with a land use plan to include:</p>
<ul class="content-listing">
<li> - Future  economic development land use areas for the LPFN main reserve and the urban properties;</li>
<li> - Zoning or designated areas and mapping for commercial, industrial, agricultural, residential, educational, traditional and spiritual, burial, recreational, roads and right-a-ways, natural areas and special areas;</li>
<li> - Draft by-laws and policies for commercial, agricultural, residential, educational, traditional and spiritual, burial, recreational, roads and right-a-ways, green space and natural areas and special areas;</li>
<li> - Draft and final First Nation Profile;</li>
<li> - Draft Environmental Management Plan;</li>
<li> - Identify future development areas;</li>
<li> - Develop maps for infrastructure, land, water, drainage and aquifer areas;</li>
<li> - Identify future parks and recreation areas;</li>
<li> - Provide an emergency plan and emergency service map;</li>
</ul>
</div>

