<p>
The First Nation Government recognizes that education for our membership is the basis of future development of the community. Present educational facilities will be officially zoned for educational purposes. Future expansion of education services and infrastructure shall be planned and zoned for educational development and services;</p>

<div class="fancy-title title-border" style="float:left; width:100%;"><h3>10.1 Long Plain School </h3></div>

<p>
Long Plain School was built in 1988 on the Southwest Quarter of Section 22 Township 10 Range 8 WPM along the Yellow quill Trail East Road. According to the Canada Land Survey Records (CLSR), the school area was surveyed in 1999 and lies in Lot 2 which is 8.42 hectares or 20.81 acres of land. The school building is 2,200 square meters or 6,661.8 square feet in size. </p>

